Practical Sockets
=================

The Practical Sockets Library 

From http://cs.ecs.baylor.edu/~donahoo/practical/CSockets/practical/
Originally by Michael J. Donahoo and Kenneth L. Calvert

To install just type:

./configure
make
make install

If you get a warning like this:    
 
WARNING: 'aclocal-1.14' is missing on your system.

Then you will need to install automake, autoconf, and libtool and run:

autoreconf

Not sure how to fix this, affects at least Debian wheezy 
 
